        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I'm aware that this is a request for NewPipe itself and that requests for adding a new service need to be made at [NewPipeExtractor](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipeExtractor/issues).\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the feature request will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one feature request.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Feature description\n\nAbility to add multiple timestamp to a video without fiction when watching in full screen or floating window. \r\nNot having to enter any title just like a bookmark button or swipe gesture to record timestamps multiple times on a video and store info with specific video. \r\nAbility to export these time stamps to clipboard after watching the video.\r\nOptional clickable links if possible to navigate to these timestamps would be nice but not necessary as purpose is mainly to export to clipboard for adding to other note apps.\r\n\n\n### Why do you want this feature?\n\nYoutube now has become a source of instant, diverse and updated information. \r\nTo eliminate  friction in processing these videos on the fly. This feature request addresses this by not worrying about remembering the time stamps of portions that are of interest is a stress free and huge time-saving solution. It also compliments the app use case for this purpose. \r\nWith the ability to export these timestams of a specific video to clipboard, allows the user to save this on any notes app of their choice for further processing and can be addon to their existing workflows.\r\nDoes save time for user, also productivity aspect would encourage more use of app as it would be unique to Android. There are chrome extensions that do this already on desktop browsers.\r\n\n\n### Additional information\n\nI would be more than happy to help with placement of button/swipe gesture and provide feedback on ui experience",
