        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I'm aware that this is a request for NewPipe itself and that requests for adding a new service need to be made at [NewPipeExtractor](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipeExtractor/issues).\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the feature request will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one feature request.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Feature description\n\nSearching in a video's comments is a very helpful feature to find information, especially for videos with hundreds of comments.\n\n### Why do you want this feature?\n\nOften, comments contain additional information or factual corrections to specific terms, which are discoverable with textual search. While the \"official\" browser client allows a browser-based search with <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>f</kbd>, it still requires to first reveal all comments via repeated manual infinite-scroll bottom triggering.\r\n\r\nAlso, a comment search feature allows to avoid to create duplicate/rudundant comment, and allows to instead upvote an existing comment in order to draw attention and give feedback to it.\r\n\r\nhttps://hadzy.com/ and https://ytcomment.kmcat.uk/ are third-party services which allow for searching in a video's comments.\n\n### Additional information\n\nSearching for \"*comment search*\" revealed hundreds of issues in NewPipe's issue list, but none of them seemed discussing *this* requested feature.\r\n\r\nIn case *NewPipe* already does have a video comment search feature, please consider *this* issue as a request for improving this feature's discoverability within the app.",
