        "body": "              Okay, it seems like providing app notifications on Android TV is a no-no: https://scribe.rip/android-tv-application-notifications-on-o-c6820ada2086\r\n\r\n@Stypox Can it be made so that errors which would generate error notifications on handhelds are made to open the error activity on TV instead?\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @opusforlife2 in https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues/9023#issuecomment-1257273798_\r\n            \r\n---\r\n\r\nAudric gave another idea: provide a menu in settings that lets the user access the error notification history since the app was last opened. I think this could also be set to a time limit like one day, one week, one month, etc.\r\n\r\nOh, and this alternative would need to show the user a toast, like \"An error occurred. Open the list of errors in settings to view it\". Or it could be a snackbar that directly provides a button to open the 'error notification history' page.",
