        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I'm aware that this is a request for NewPipe itself and that requests for adding a new service need to be made at [NewPipeExtractor](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipeExtractor/issues).\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the feature request will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one feature request.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Feature description\n\nLogo redesign, to reflect the changes that are coming to NewPipe.\r\nA more mature and modern look that is more distinct and less generic (many logos look very similar to the current one).\r\n\r\nMy proposal is a subtle change, based around the letter P, not just a play button.\r\nP for Pipe and P for Privacy (a core feature of the app). But yes, also for Play :)\r\n\r\n![newpipegithub](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/assets/143116714/1da88cf1-1738-40c4-9e9c-c8ee0d5eb91d)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe color is a more intense red (#CD0100). \r\nThe symbol incorporates the circle of the original icon shape, but is nested inside a rounded square, which looks more stablished.\n\n### Why do you want this feature?\n\nWith the NewPipe that is to come (more modern and stable), i think the logo/icon should also reflect the change.\r\n\r\nI think the current one is good, but looks a little generic, and it seems just like a play button in small sizes.\r\nJust a few similar ones from Google Images, most of them media player apps.\r\n\r\n![newpipesimilares](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/assets/143116714/09d6aac0-54e1-4a67-82d5-1285069714d6)\r\n\r\nNewPipe is an established project in the privacy and open source community and the brand should be in tune with that.\r\nThe change of direction for the project is a pretty fitting moment to update the brand.\r\n\n\n### Additional information\n\nDesign process and ideas\r\n\r\n![newpipeproceso](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/assets/143116714/ebc7c2f8-83a6-4df7-8283-d69627d281dd)\r\n",
