        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I am able to reproduce the bug with the [latest version](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/releases/latest).\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the bug report will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one bug.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Affected version\n\n0.25.0\n\n### Steps to reproduce the bug\n\n1. Press select on the open drawer button.\r\n2. Scroll down to Toggle Service and press select.\r\n3. Scroll down the list. You'll notice you won't be able to reach the dropdown list to change Peer Tube instances.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nYou should be able to scroll over to the dropdown list and click on it.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nYou can move to the checkbox that shows your currently selected Peer Tube instance, but if you scroll down again, it will jump past the Peer Tube service selecter dropdown and over to the next option (Bandcamp in this case).\n\n### Screenshots/Screen recordings\n\n_No response_\n\n### Logs\n\n_No response_\n\n### Affected Android/Custom ROM version\n\nFire OS 7.6.3.3\n\n### Affected device model\n\nFire Stick Gen 3\n\n### Additional information\n\nThis issue can possibly be fixed if the dropdown list was a button instead, and if it had a label such as \"Change current Peer Tube Instance\".",
